verbose_text: Compared with free CPT having an area under the curve (AUC) of 364.69 mug h/L and an elimination half-life (t 1/2 Beta) of 7.51 h, GAI@CP displayed increased AUC of 930.69 mug h/L (2.55 fold) and enlarged t 1/2 Beta of 36.84 h (4.91 fold), which indicated that GAI@P significantly prolonged the blood circulation time and increased the stability of CPT because of the stealthy surface.
evidence: GAI@P significantly prolonged the blood circulation time and increased the stability of CPT
